Lectures are hand-written notes based so do attend. Her explanation and logic are the key. Tests are similar to pt, which are always posted with solutions. Be sure to review class notes thoroughly because tests cover almost everything taught. Although her final can be tricky (both 208 and 325), she always makes adjustments, and TA is amazing too!

rComments: Lectures are skippable- she basically just reads alouds slides. Just do all your readings and youll be fine. She's super approachable so find her in office hours if you've questions. Just do past exam papers and you will be ok. And she will give you clear insights on what to study for in particular before exams. Or just email her- she replies!

Alexopoulos was a great prof. Her tests and finals are not hard as long as you practised her past finals and her problem sets a lot. She's nice and it's not too hard to ge an A in her course I had severe hand cramps from writing her notes down and her tests are long! Overall best prof for 325 and much better than Fuster who didnt explain clearly!
